The paper describes a robotic system for autonomous kitting in automotive logistics, which involves various tasks such as detection and pose estimation of transport boxes, part segmentation, recognition of part variants, grasp generation, and arm trajectory optimization. These tasks require expertise in robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
